<subSubSection id="91BC0ED38B4C905DFF55FC401578FB9C" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="D9195D588B4C905DFF55FC40155FFC68" blockId="8.[189,324,952,978]" box="[189,324,952,978]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<heading id="8251EA348B4C905DFF55FC40155FFC68" bold="true" box="[189,324,952,978]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" reason="3">
<emphasis id="EBD2814A8B4C905DFF55FC40155FFC68" bold="true" box="[189,324,952,978]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D9195D588B4C905DFF55FC101578FB9C" blockId="8.[189,1398,1000,1062]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
The name is derived from the Latin word ‘ 
<emphasis id="EBD2814A8B4C905DFD2CFC101729FBB8" box="[708,818,1000,1026]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">flagellum</emphasis>
’, meaning ‘whip’, which refers to the whip-like flagellosigma.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="91BC0ED38B4C905DFF55FBB615B7FAB9" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="D9195D588B4C905DFF55FBB6152DFBD2" blockId="8.[189,310,1102,1128]" box="[189,310,1102,1128]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<heading id="8251EA348B4C905DFF55FBB6152DFBD2" bold="true" box="[189,310,1102,1128]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" reason="3">
<emphasis id="EBD2814A8B4C905DFF55FBB6152DFBD2" bold="true" box="[189,310,1102,1128]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D9195D588B4C905DFF55FB8515B7FAB9" blockId="8.[189,1399,1149,1283]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<taxonomicName id="1EA626DB8B4C905DFF55FB851529FB2D" authorityName="Grant" authorityYear="1841" box="[189,306,1149,1175]" class="Demospongiae" family="Chalinidae" genus="Haliclona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplosclerida" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="EBD2814A8B4C905DFF55FB851529FB2D" box="[189,306,1149,1175]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Haliclona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-like sponges possessing a spiculation of oxeas, flagellosigmas (asymmetrical sigmas with unequal length and unequal shape of inward curved endings) and symmetrical (normal-shaped) sigmas. Skeletal reticulation loosely organized, unispicular, paucispicular or polyspicular, bound by variable amounts of spongin.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="91BC0ED38B4C905CFF55FAD31102FEFD" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="10" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="D9195D588B4C905DFF55FAD31534FAFF" blockId="8.[189,303,1323,1349]" box="[189,303,1323,1349]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<heading id="8251EA348B4C905DFF55FAD31534FAFF" bold="true" box="[189,303,1323,1349]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" reason="3">
<emphasis id="EBD2814A8B4C905DFF55FAD31534FAFF" bold="true" box="[189,303,1323,1349]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D9195D588B4C905DFF55FAA21101F9D5" blockId="8.[189,1399,1370,1647]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
This subgenus shares with mainstream 
<taxonomicName id="1EA626DB8B4C905DFD69FAA216EDFACE" authorityName="Grant" authorityYear="1841" box="[641,758,1370,1396]" class="Demospongiae" family="Chalinidae" genus="Haliclona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplosclerida" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="EBD2814A8B4C905DFD69FAA216EDFACE" box="[641,758,1370,1396]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Haliclona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species a skeleton in which the ascending spicule tracts are interconnected by single megascleres. There is usually no distinct detachable ectosomal skeleton, although tangential arrangement of the oxeas at the surface is common. The choanosomal skeleton tends to be very loosely organized, verging to confused. In that aspect it conforms most closely to species of the subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="1EA626DB8B4C905DFE69FA1115CDF9B9" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1867" box="[385,470,1513,1539]" class="Demospongiae" family="Chalinidae" genus="Gellius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplosclerida" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="EBD2814A8B4C905DFE69FA1115CDF9B9" box="[385,470,1513,1539]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Gellius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but in that subgenus the sigmas are symmetrical and often angular. Although symmetrical normal sigmas are part of the spicule complement of the new subgenus, these are never angular. The habitus of members of the subgenus varies strongly, from small crusts to elaborate plates or arborescent forms. Association with other sponges or other sessile organisms appears common.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D9195D588B4C905DFF55F96F1744F96F" blockId="8.[189,1398,1687,1749]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">The subgenus is found all over the world’s oceans. The depth occurrence is wide, but so far is confined to coastal, continental platform and upper bathyal waters.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D9195D588B4C905DFF55F905107AF8E5" blockId="8.[189,1399,1789,1887]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Ten species are recognized here, four of which are new to science, one is given a new name due to junior homonymy, and one remains unnamed due to limited available material. From the historical overview presented above it is likely that several more species will be found to be extant.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D9195D588B4C905DFF55F87F116CF853" blockId="8.[189,1399,1927,2025]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
It would perhaps have been logical to choose 
<taxonomicName id="1EA626DB8B4C905DFD21F87F1051F81B" authorityName="Van Soest" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Ridley &amp; Dendy" baseAuthorityYear="1886" box="[713,1098,1927,1953]" class="Demospongiae" family="Chalinidae" genus="Haliclona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplosclerida" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="flagellifera" subGenus="Flagellia">
<emphasis id="EBD2814A8B4C905DFD21F87F1725F81B" box="[713,830,1927,1953]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Haliclona</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="EBD2814A8B4C905DFCA6F87F17A1F81B" box="[846,954,1927,1953]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Flagellia</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="EBD2814A8B4C905DFC21F87F1051F81B" box="[969,1098,1927,1953]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">flagellifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as the type species for the new subgenus as it is the most closely associated name to species belonging to 
<taxonomicName id="1EA626DB8B4C905DFB86F85310C1F87F" authority="Van Soest, 2017" authorityName="Van Soest" authorityYear="2017" box="[1134,1242,1963,1989]" class="Demospongiae" family="Chalinidae" genus="Haliclona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplosclerida" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Porifera" rank="subGenus" status="subgen. nov." subGenus="Flagellia">
<emphasis id="EBD2814A8B4C905DFB86F85310C1F87F" box="[1134,1242,1963,1989]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Flagellia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="F0E13C318B4C905DFB0AF853116CF87F" box="[1250,1399,1963,1989]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" rank="subGenus">subgen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(cf. the historical overview above). However, the 
<typeStatus id="061DE3FA8B4C905DFCEEF8371776F853" box="[774,877,1999,2025]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<emphasis id="EBD2814A8B4C905DFC7DF82817B1F853" box="[917,938,2000,2025]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">H</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="1EA626DB8B4C905DFC51F8371076F853" authority="Van Soest, 2017" authorityName="Van Soest" authorityYear="2017" box="[953,1133,1999,2025]" class="Demospongiae" family="Chalinidae" genus="Haliclona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplosclerida" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="indonesiae" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Flagellia">
(
<emphasis id="EBD2814A8B4C905DFC2BF82817CEF853" box="[963,981,2000,2025]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">F</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis id="EBD2814A8B4C905DFC06F8371076F853" box="[1006,1133,1999,2025]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">indonesiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="F0E13C318B4C905DFB9DF83710CBF853" box="[1141,1232,1999,2025]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
was collected
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D9195D588B4D905CFF55FEF21102FEFD" blockId="9.[189,1399,266,327]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
recently and is also quite large in size making subsampling for DNA sequencing a viable option for nearfuture phylogenetic studies of the position of 
<taxonomicName id="1EA626DB8B4D905CFD3BFED51724FEFD" authority="Van Soest, 2017" authorityName="Van Soest" authorityYear="2017" box="[723,831,301,327]" class="Demospongiae" family="Chalinidae" genus="Haliclona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplosclerida" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Porifera" rank="subGenus" status="subgen. nov." subGenus="Flagellia">
<emphasis id="EBD2814A8B4D905CFD3BFED51724FEFD" box="[723,831,301,327]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Flagellia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="F0E13C318B4D905CFCADFED517C2FEFD" box="[837,985,301,327]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" rank="subGenus">subgen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
in the order 
<taxonomicName id="1EA626DB8B4D905CFB87FED5110DFEFD" authorityName="Topsent" authorityYear="1928" box="[1135,1302,301,327]" class="Demospongiae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplosclerida" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Porifera" rank="order">Haplosclerida</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
